Context: The Good Food Market at St. James Campus is a weekly non-profit fruit and vegetable market run in partnership with FoodShare Toronto. It supports convenient, low-cost access to fresh, nutritious food and advocates for student food security. All students and GBC community members are welcome. Pre-order forms are sent out every week, email goodfoodmarket@georgebrown.ca to be added to the mailing list. The market takes place on Thursdays (except intersession week) from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. It is located in front of the Bookstore (Campus Store) at St James Campus (SJA), 200 King Street East. For more information, visit the social media hub or sign up for updates. Contact George Brown College at 416-415-2000 or TTY: 1-877-515-5559. For further inquiries email ask.george@georgebrown.ca. Please note that the information contained on this website is subject to change without notice. The market's dates, times and location are factual information.
